  "text": "As for the European population, we estimated whether the observed number of polymorphic sites in regions 4-9 (S obs ¼ 56; see Table 2 ) is significantly different from expectations under the standard neutral model. Given an expected heterozygosity of 0.0127 [CITATION_1] , 41-251 segregating sites would be expected. The observation of 56 SNPs is therefore not significantly different from neutral expectations (P ¼ 0.07). However, it should be noted that the u estimates for loci 6 and 7 are significantly low ( Table 2 ). The multi-locus HKA test [CITATION_2] did not reveal any significant [CITATION_3] for n ¼ 12 lines. Fragments significantly devoid of segregating sites are in italics. *, significant at the 0.05 level; **, significant at the 0.01 level.",
